<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Upload media files to configurable storage locations and create tiddlers with `_canonical_uri`. When a tiddler is renamed or deleted, the physical file and all derived artifacts follow automatically.

!! Features

* ''Location registry'' &mdash; define multiple file storage locations (built-in `/files/`, scattered-binaries auto-discovered, user-created). Managed via tag-based tiddler convention.
* ''Upload'' &mdash; drop files onto `<$file-dropzone>` with `location` attribute to target any writable location
* ''Thumbnails'' &mdash; automatic thumbnail generation for images and PDFs via ImageMagick (configurable resolution)
* ''Thumbnail rendering'' &mdash; show thumbnails instead of full-size files by default, with click-to-expand and toolbar toggle
* ''Rename'' &mdash; renaming a tiddler renames the file on writable locations (including `_generated/` thumbnails) and cascades to artifact tiddlers
* ''Delete'' &mdash; deleting a tiddler offers to delete the file on writable locations and automatically cleans up all derived artifacts (extractions, summaries, etc.)
* ''Artifact cascade'' &mdash; derived tiddlers tagged with `_artifact_source` are automatically renamed/deleted when the parent file tiddler changes
* ''EXIF extraction'' &mdash; auto-extract metadata (date, camera, GPS location, dimensions, exposure settings) from uploaded images and write to tiddler fields via configurable field mapping (global + per-location overrides)
* ''Deduplication'' &mdash; optional global content-hash dedup skips uploads of identical files
* ''MIME whitelist'' &mdash; only allowed file types can be uploaded
* ''Settings UI'' &mdash; location management, thumbnail config, and media types in ControlPanel &rarr; Settings &rarr; File Upload

!! Quick start

Add a dropzone to any tiddler:

```
<$file-dropzone actions="""
<$action-createtiddler
  $basetitle=<<filename>>
  _canonical_uri=<<canonical-uri>>
  _thumbnail_uri=<<generated-uri>>
  _content_hash=<<content-hash>>
  type=<<type>>
/>
""">
Drop files here
</$file-dropzone>
```

Drop a file &rarr; the file-paths filter routes it to the right subfolder: images to `files/images/`, PDFs to `files/pdf/`. A tiddler is created with `_canonical_uri`. If thumbnails are enabled, `_thumbnail_uri` points to the generated thumbnail in `_generated/`.

Use the [[test tab|$:/plugins/rimir/file-upload/test]] in the plugin detail view to try it out.

